    },
    {
      "line": 35,
      "text": "What follows is a self-scoring test on basic environmental perception of place. Scoring is done on the"
    },
    {
      "line": 36,
      "text": "honor system, so if you fudge, cheat, or elude, you also get an idea of where you're at. The quiz is"
    },
    {
      "line": 37,
      "text": "culture bound, favoring those people who live in the country over city dwellers, and scores can be"
    },
    {
      "line": 38,
      "text": "adjusted accordingly. Most of the questions, however, are of such a basic nature that undue allowances"
    },
    {
      "line": 41,
      "text": "are not necessary."
    },
    {
      "line": 44,
      "text": "1. Trace the water you drink from precipitation"
    },
    {
      "line": 45,
      "text": "to tap."
    },
    {
      "line": 48,
      "text": "2. How many days till the moon is full? (Slack"
    },
    {
      "line": 49,
      "text": "of two days allowed.)"
    },
    {
      "line": 52,
      "text": "What soil series are you standing on?"
    },
    {
      "line": 55,
      "text": "What was the total rainfall in your area last"
    },
    {
      "line": 56,
      "text": "year (July-June)? (Slack: 1” for every 20”.)"
    },
    {
      "line": 59,
      "text": "When was the last time a fire burned your area?"
    },
    {
      "line": 62,
      "text": "6. What were the primary subsistence techniques"
    },
    {
      "line": 63,
      "text": "of the culture that lived in your area"
    },
    {
      "line": 64,
      "text": "before you?"
    },
    {
      "line": 67,
      "text": "Name five native edible plants in your region"
    },
    {
